parameters:
Priestess Sophia: Oh, this is quite splendid for a military
encampment.

Clea: Is that so? The Goats' encampment was even more
splendid though.

Priestess Sophia: That place is more like a city in name
only. Are they planning to wipe out the goblins of Oros?

Mage Relm: It's impossible to completely wipe them out!
Even with the empire expanding this much, there are still
enough damages occurring.

Thief Nora: There are so many strong-looking people here.
Are they really just hunting in the mountains...?
Clea: Let's confirm the details with General Atu.

Mage Relm: It's getting noisy. Could it be that goblins
have arrived!?

Thief Nora: I don't think so. I don't smell the unpleasant
scent of goblins...

Imperial Soldier: As I mentioned before, the recruitment
has ended. We are no longer seeking any collaborators!
General Atu: What's all this noise about?

Imperial Soldier: I apologize, but this person insists on
participating in the subjugation.

General Atu: Hahaha, you're quite lively for an old man!
Words are unnecessary between warriors... If you want to
talk, then draw your sword.

General Atu: What's the matter, feeling scared? If you want
to voice your opinion to me, then take up your sword.

One-armed Opro: That belongs to you, doesn't it? I won't
use someone else's weapon... Besides, I'm already prepared.
General Atu: Oh... then don't hold back.

General Atu: Can you stop my first strike... Where were
you?

One-armed Opro: In the fields and mountains... before the
grotesque monsters.

General Atu: That one-armed strength... it's the one-armed
Opro!

One-armed Opro: General Atu, the hero of the battlefield...
It is an honor to have you know my name.

General Atu: If you are the famous Goblin Slayer, please
come inside the tent. I would like to receive advice from
you.
Cleric Sophia: I wonder if we are no longer needed~

Clea: First, let's report and there might be something I
can help with.

Imperial Soldier: No abnormalities! This place is
dangerous, so please get off.

Imperial Soldier: I was brought here for military service,
specifically goblin hunting... I wonder if I'll be able to
return to Fortizona alive...

Imperial Soldier: I was brought here for military service,
specifically goblin hunting... I wonder if I'll be able to
return to Fortizona alive...

Imperial Soldier: I'm a veteran of the Tarasa War, but I've
never faced anything other than humans, so I'm nervous.

Imperial Soldier: I'm a veteran of the Tarasa War, but I've
never faced anything other than humans, so I'm nervous.

Imperial Soldier: Did you come for comfort... Oh my! Please
keep this a secret from General Atu, I beg you.

Imperial Soldier: Did you come for comfort... Oh my! Please
keep this a secret from General Atu, I beg you.

General Atu: Ah, it's you guys! Well then, let's end the
conversation here.

Royal Court Official Emoni: I understand that you are a
hero! However, neglecting the royal palace is not
acceptable, don't you think?

Royal Court Official Emoni: The fact that you conducted a
public recruitment without permission... Queen Caron-sama is
extremely furious!
General Atu: I see... In that case...

General Atu: You little girl, if you dare to voice your
opinion to me on the battlefield, let your sword do the
talking!

Royal Court Official Emoni: H-huh...! Um, I, well... th-
that's not it!

Royal Court Official Emoni: G- General, you have
misunderstood! I-I was just, um, just confirming, yes,
confirming things!

General Atu: Hahaha, then it's settled! You guys should
wait for the results at the royal palace!

General Atu: Well then, let's have a detailed conversation
inside with the guest from the Adventurer's Guild, shall
we?
Royal Court Official Emoni: Adventurer's Guild...!

Royal Court Official Emoni: Are you a member of the
Adventurer's Guild? Ohohoho, the quality has dropped quite a
bit while I wasn't looking!

Royal Court Official Emoni: If Emoni ever loses her job in
Agonia, please let her become your subordinate anytime.

Royal Court Official Emoni: Well then, General Atu, I shall
take my leave! I will be waiting for good news at the royal
palace!

General Atu: That Caron woman's pawn, she has the audacity
to step onto the battlefield with her dirty feet...

Royal Court Official Emoni: Who are you? I'm busy, so
please refrain from talking to me.
A terrifyingly sharp greatsword is piercing through.
A terrifyingly sharp greatsword is piercing through.

Imperial Soldier: General Atu is the eldest brother of the
Imperial Army! It's an honor for a soldier to die under the
General's command.

Imperial Soldier: General Atu is the eldest brother of the
Imperial Army! It's an honor for a soldier to die under the
General's command.
Clea: I went to see the request form from Oros.

Imperial Soldier: Everyone...! I have heard of your
achievements in defeating the ogres!
Clea: Is this request about subjugating goblins?

Imperial Soldier: Many of Oros' soldiers are stationed in
places related to the crystal.

Imperial Soldier: Although the number of goblins has
decreased, we cannot completely prevent damage in the poorly
fortified garrisons.

Imperial Soldier: That's why! We need the power of someone
like you!

Mage Relm: Me!? Well, I am indeed a genius who surpasses
even the hardworking prodigies, but...
Priestess Sophia: Hehe, it's cute how you say it yourself.

Imperial Soldier: First, please try smelling this medicinal
herb.

Thief Nora: T-This smell is terrible! If I can't smell food
anymore, it'll be a problem!

Imperial Soldier: This is a medicinal herb that grows
naturally in the Sazani Grasslands. Our comrades have
discovered that goblins avoid this herb.

Priestess Sophia: I would like to hear the reason for
requesting our help, despite having that medicinal herb.

Imperial Soldier: We're not exactly sure of its
effectiveness, but it is certain that the goblins are
avoiding it. However, there are cases where they don't run
away either.

Imperial Soldier: We would like to request your assistance
in verifying the effectiveness of the medicinal herb and
defeating any individuals who may have developed resistance
to it.
Imperial Soldier: Actually, there is one more request...

Mage Relm: I understand. So, you want me to refine the
medicinal herb and make medicine, right?

Imperial Soldier: Please, we don't want to see our comrades
falling one by one.
Clea: Understood, leave it to me.

Mage Relm: First, let's verify its effectiveness. Let's go
to the Sazani Grasslands.
Imperial Soldier: Please take care of my comrades as well!

Imperial Soldier: Do you know the secret of the medicinal
herbs!?

Mage Relm: It seems that freshness is affecting it. It
seems that goblins tend to dislike fresher ones.

Mage Relm: I think we won't be able to figure out what
goblins dislike without returning to the academy.

Imperial Soldier: We have picked medicinal herbs! Please
use these for the production of medicine!

Mage Relm: Not only deciphering, but also refining... Even
for a genius like me, I'll need some time!

Imperial Soldier: If there is hope, we can fight. Besides,
just scattering medicinal herbs might have some effect.

Mage Relm: I'll do my best to hurry, so please make sure
you don't die, okay?
Imperial Soldier: Please take care of my comrades as well!
Mage Relm: This is the prototype that was requested.

Imperial Soldier: So fast...! Truly the genius of the
Magic Academy!

Mage Relm: If I give it my all, this is what I can create.
But please remember, this is just a prototype, so don't have
too much confidence in it.

Imperial Soldier: We will request the Oros for the handover
research. Thank you for your cooperation!

Imperial Soldier: This is the reward and our gratitude from
us.

Imperial Soldier: Thanks to you, the damage has
dramatically decreased. Please provide us with a more
effective medicine!
